13 Amend the amendment by inserting after Part X the following:
14 'PART Y
15 Sec. Y-1. 22 MRSA §4302-A, sub-§1, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 575, §1, is
16 amended to read:
17 1. Training required. No later than the 120th day after appointment or election, and
18 annually thereafter, an overseer, municipal official designated by the overseers to
19 administer this chapter and any municipal official appointed to administer this chapter shall
20 complete training on the requirements of this chapter.
21 Sec. Y-2. 22 MRSA §4302-A, sub-§3 is enacted to read:
22 3. Communication of program requirements. The department annually shall
23 transmit to an overseer, municipal official designated by the overseers to administer this
24 chapter and any municipal official appointed to administer this chapter information about
25 the rules, requirements and compliance expectations of the municipal general assistance
26 program.
27 Sec. Y-3. 22 MRSA §4308, sub-§1-A, as enacted by PL 2011, c. 655, Pt. R, §2, is
28 amended to read:
29 1-A. Limit on housing assistance. Except as provided in subsections 1‑B and 2,
30 housing assistance provided pursuant to this chapter is limited to a maximum of 9 12
31 months during the period from July 1, 2012 to June 30, 2013 in a 36-month period per
32 household, except for temporary housing and emergency shelters, as defined by the
33 department by rule.
